abstract: BANGKOK, July 31 -- The uneasiness among the people here, far from lessening, is increasing. Seven more French gunboats have arrived at Koh-si-Chang, making a total of thirteen now there. Negotiations are still going on, but the progress made is not reported. The intentions of the French are awaited with fear and apprehension.

abstract: -- Louis Irig died in Whitney, Neb., last Friday morning, after a prolonged sleep of three months. He had been almost blind, but was a tireless worker and in good health until the beginning of his prolonged nap. The medical fraternity could not discover its cause. He had only two waking intervals -- once he was awake and talked lucidly for an hour and at the other time he staid awake only ten minutes.

abstract: BOSTON, Aug. 5 -- Beyond the strength and scarcity of New-York funds, there was little news of interest at the Clearing House this morning. abstract: CHICAGO, Aug. 11 -- The best wheat market in months developed to-day. The cash price is up 3c a bushel. For the September option there was an advance of 2 1/2c, and the closing was steady within 1/8c from the top figures. The low crop estimates, light receipts, and better financial outlook were the main reasons. Corn broke on the rains over the West, and only scored a net gain of 1/8c.

abstract: SARATOGA, N.Y., Aug. 12. -- A very large attendance assembled on the Saratoga race-track grounds to-day to greet the Saratoga Racing Association's first annual garden party. In the steeplechase Jockey Callahan was thrown from Ballarat and badly injured.

abstract: EYES OF DEEP-SEA FISH. -- The eyes of deep-sea fish are very varied; some have neither eyes nor eight; others have greatly enlarged eyeballs, so as to catch the least glimpse of light. abstract: CHICAGO, Aug. 14 -- It was largely the stock market that disturbed grain to-day. The action of prices in Wall Street and a break in quotations for Chicago cable securities operated to unsettle the trade. Compared with Saturday night, wheat to-night is 1 1/4 @ 1 1/2 c lower. abstract: CONEY ISLAND, Aug. 15 -- On the padded stage of the Coney Island Athletic Club, an arena dedicated to fistic war, King John Y. McKane, Lord Absolute of the island, stood to day and made a peace offering. abstract: CHICAGO, Ill., Aug. 16 -- Trade in wheat was moderately active to-day. In corn and oats it was light, while in provisions the brokers ensconced themselves in their arm chairs and went to sleep. The tendency of prices was downward. abstract: FAR ROCKAWAY, L.I., Aug. 22. -- The town was excited to-night over a chase by the police after a negro who had assaulted Miss Mamie McPhillips of New-York, who is living with her parents in a cottage here. abstract: Jacob Weissbaum made love to Matilda Walter shortly after their first acquaintance in the November of 1891. abstract: ST. LOUIS, Mo., Aug. 27 -- When John N. abstract: SAN ANTONIO, Texas, Aug. 30 -- A double tragedy is reported from the little town of Sonora, is Sutton County. He made his way to the little town of Sonora, where he had relatives, and soon secured a position as laborer and made many warm friends.

abstract: HARRISBURG, Penn., Aug. 30 -- The Republican Convention which met in this city to-day was a harmonious gathering. The hour set for the meeting was 10 o'clock but the sight of a street parade made by a visiting circus delayed the delegates for forty-five minutes. After the gayly-decked vans and band wagons had disappeared beyond Capitol Hill, Chairman J. Howard Reeder of the State Committee called the convention to order. There were 253 delegates present.
